hopobject.body: We used to work together declinol uk reviews In a damning report China Labor Watch said Pegatron was "violating a great number of international and Chinese laws and standards", adding that Apple's code of conduct was being flaunted. The organisation went even further, claiming that Apple's own standards violated Chinese law, saying, "Apple heralded that its suppliers had achieved 99 percent compliance with Apple's 60-hour workweek rule, this despite the fact that 60 hours is a direct violation of China's 49-hour statutory limit."
